Short Response:
1) The Linux command to rename a file is mv. The command to copy a file is 
cp.
2) Middle clicking in vim in insert mode acts as a paste function - 
whatever's in the clipboard at the moment gets pasted into vim. If someone
middle clicks while having text selected, the selected text gets replaced
by the clipboard text.
3) The name of the application that processes commands on the command 
line is the terminal.
4) 
5) Entering :split in command mode in vim splits the screen in vim and lets 
you open two different files in the same window.
6) 
